sentences: Anca Parghel attended the Iaşi Music Conservatory, from which she graduated in 1981, having as primary instrument piano, and secondary bel canto.
At the age of 18 she married painter Virgiliu Parghel (divorced 2001), with whom she had two sons, Ciprian and Tudor, who became jazz musicians themselves.
She lived in Bucharest in the first part of the 1990s, before moving to Brussels in 1997.
She was a Professor of vocal jazz at the Royal Conservatory in Brussels and the Lemmens Institute in Leuven (1997–2002).
She lived in Brussels for eight years before making a return to her home country around 2005.
She performed in Canada, most notably at the Rimouski Jazz Festival 2003 where she preceded and eclipsed famed French singer Anne Ducros (cf.
Rimouski local press, in early September 2003 reporting on "Rimouski Festi Jazz"), and sporadically in the United States (2003–2006).
Her concert in Danville, Virginia, at the North Theater on November 10, 2006, was played to an enchanted full house and created a local sensation (cf.
Anca Parghel recorded an electro-pop album in 2007, and submitted the tune "Brasil" to National Selection Contest 2008 for Eurovision.

sentences: Anca Parghel (September 16, 1957– December 5, 2008) was a Romanian of roma ethnicity  jazz singer, composer, arranger, pianist, choir conductor and music teacher.
Early years =

She made unannounced late night appearances at jazz clubs in New York City, where she played with the local bands led either by Pat Higgins at the "Lennox Lounge", "St. Nick's Pub" or by Manny Duran at Cleopatra's Needle.
She appeared on stage one month prior to her passing.
